Description: Oval handle sliver of a probably KLnidian pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay medium-coarse brown; some mica. Circular stamp with prow symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 62, 4. Börker, Chr., 'Die Herkunft der Schiffsbugel-Stempel' in Empereur, J.-Y. and Garlan, Y. (eds), Recherches sur les Amphores Grecques [BCH suppl. XIII], Paris 1986, 474 fig. 4. Name Kleandros.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0356)
